# -Active-Directory-Password-Reset-Account-Lockout-Lab
Password reset and account lockout 
## Overview
This lab demonstrates common IT Support and Active Directory administration tasks in a Windows Server environment.

## Lab Environment
- Windows Server 2022
- Windows 10 Client Machine
- VMware Workstation 17
- Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)

## Tasks Performed

### 1. Created Domain Users
- Created users inside Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)

### 2. Password Reset
- Reset user passwords from the domain controller
- Configured temporary passwords

### 3. Forced Password Change
- Enabled:
  - "User must change password at next logon"

### 4. Troubleshooting Login Issues
- Diagnosed password mismatch issues
- Verified keyboard layout and policy synchronization

### 5. Configured Account Lockout Policy
Using Group Policy Management:
- Set account lockout threshold
- Configured lockout duration
- Applied policies using:
```powershell
gpupdate /force
```

### 6. Simulated Account Lockout
- Entered multiple incorrect passwords on client machine
- Triggered account lockout successfully

# Unlocking User Accounts
- Unlocked locked user accounts from Active Directory

### 8. Network Verification
Tested communication between client and domain controller:
```powershell
ping 192.168.134.10
```

# Skills Learned
- Active Directory Administration
- Password Management
- Group Policy Configuration
- IT Support Troubleshooting
- Windows Server Administration
- Account Security Management

